Vernacular Names:
—Pintadinho (
Brazil
: Northern region), Coco d’óleo (
Brazil
: Southeastern region); Isnepa, Cari-cari, Cari-cari blanco, Pajarillo, Toco, Tasaa (
Bolivia
); Tepemisque, Tepemiste, Plumillo (
Guatemala
); Harrino (
Panama
); Memble, Memble-amarillo, Memblón de bajío, Frijolillo (
El Salvador
); Cedro-pashaco (
Peru
); Guayacán, Llovizno, Hoja menuda (
Colombia
); Abey-hembra, Abey-heurbra, Palo-tranquilo, Tengue (
Cuba
), Corazón bonito, Guaje, Quebracho blanco, Quebracho and Quiebra-hacho (
Mexico
). The latter two names are also reported for the related genus, 

Dialium

, which also occurs in 
Mexico
and Central America and for several other exceptionally hardwood tree genera.

